Text.string: Hey, guys! Thanks for fixin' my little death-laser problem. Morale is soaring!
You're welcome. So, you said you know where the last Key fragment is?
Well, and, uh... please don't be mad... I have the third key fragment here in Atlas Headquarters.
You've been keeping that from us the whole time? I knew we couldn't trust a guy with a mustache.

It's a SIEGE mustache, okay? Look, Key fragments are worth billions. The research benefits alone could keep Atlas profitable for decades. I've already done some experiments with it, some... taste tests, that sort of thing, but at this point... you've earned it.
Cool. Well. We still want it, even if you licked it.
No spoilers, but I hope you like sour apple. Come down to Atlas and I'll have Zer0 let you in through the secret VIP entrance.
Nice place, Rhys. I'm gonna enjoy watching it burn from the inside out.

Get over it, Katagawa! You can't hold the city, the Key fragment's slipped through your fingers, and NOW you're losing your grasp on reality! THAT'S THREE HAND THINGS RIGHT THERE! Y-You can't get past my defense turrets!
Maybe I can't—but your friend Zer0 can.
Breach! All troops to the courtyard! Where the hell is Zer0?!
Without the turrets, we're sitting ducks! We cannot lose Atlas!
Contacts to the north and south! We've got mechs coming over the walls!
Maliwan on the ground! Atlas forces, retreat to the tower! Establish a perimeter!
They're everywhere! We can't hold 'em back much longer!
If we keep losing turrets, there won't be any defenses to turn back on! Hurry!
Your best bud Zer0's stabbed you in the back! How's it feel, Rhys?
Shut up, Katagawa! Zer0 would never betray me.
Rhys, it looks like Zer0 murdered all the defense personnel!
Rhys? It looks like Zer0 killed everyone.
Rhys, Zer0 is hunting down your soldiers.
Your boys are all cut up, brother! Looks like Zer0's turned.
No! No, no, no-no-no. Zer0's loyalty is not in question. Wherever he is, he must have a good reason. YOU just focus on kicking out Maliwan!
Ha-hah, YEAH! Courtyard defenses are back online! Ooh, if we can get the rear defenses up too, we might actually survive this! Head through Atlas tower—my troops are still holding it.
Eat it, Katagawa! Eat that tasty Atlas tech!
They're in the lobby! We're going to hold them off from—what? Zer0? What are you—ghlrghhrgh!
Soldier, don't you dare use your last words to slander Zer0! Say you're being murdered by someone else!
I super meant it... arghlrgrhrl.
Rhys, I don't even want Atlas anymore. Your brand is over. I'll make more profit selling your employee's organs than your guns.
Damn you, Katagawa! My brand!
The Maliwan command ship is over our rear courtyard. If we get the turrets to take it down, this whole assault falls flat on its face! Get rid of those nullhounds!
Turrets are down! Rhys, you got any more firepower?
The turrets are gone! Rhys, we're running out of options!
The turrets are dead! Do you have a backup plan?
Turrets are gone. We need a new plan, Rhys!

Aw, crap! Uhh, uh... okay! W-We left the Viper Drive in the orbital laser, right? Uh, maybe it's got enough juice left to take out that command ship! Heh-heh... you gotta hold them off while I get it working!
Come on... okay, I'm connected to the Viper Drive! It's still working! We can do this!
It wants a password! Uh, ha, did I... did I set a password on this? Uh, hmmm.
Yeah, I'm on it! Just, uh—ooh, there's a hint button. “Best frogurt flavor.” Oh, come on, Me, that could be ANYTHING!
It's beautiful, hahahaha! It's so beautiful! Oh, wow! I am legitimately crying! Hoooo! Thank you. Thank you, Vault Hunter. Atlas is... is safe. Now I just, ah, have to find Zer0.
Oh, don't worry about Zer0, Rhys. He'll find you.

Your mindgames won't work, Katagawa! Zer0's on my side. Oh, oh—see, see? He, he just walked in. I'm looking at him right now. Zer0, man—MAN, everyone's just completely lost their... what?! Zer0, what are you doing?! No—no-no-no-no-NO!

You just don't get it, do you, Rhys? This whole war could have been nice and quick. I move in, take Promethea, and make Atlas a subsidiary of Maliwan. Then I make YOU Vice President of Beach Drinks. We all win. That's how it works! That's how it's always worked!

You were special, Rhys! I saw that! You brought this bottom-shelf company back from the dead! With you in the family, we could have turned Maliwan into a universal monopoly! You and me! Brothers, selling the only weapons anyone would ever need in all six galaxies!
But I reached out my hand... and you spat in it, Rhys. So now you're not family. You're just the competition.
Zer0, c-come on, man! I thought we were friends!
You should have joined the family, Rhys.
Like I said, Zer0. I super trusted you the whole time, and it was completely justified!
Zer0, where were you?
Zer0, where the hell were you?
Zer0, I feared you had betrayed us.
You disappeared on us, Zer0.
I was on the hunt. / Could not give myself away. / Radio silence.

As for you, Vault Hunter. I owe you everything. You've fought off an all-out corporate assault, saved my company and killed my creepy business stalker. But before I give you this Key fragment, I have one last thing to ask of you: am I pulling off this mustache or what?
Once you get to the secret VIP entrance, Zer0 will let you in.
Katagawa's been quiet. He must still be pissed off that we blew up his ship. Weirdo's probably cryin' somewhere in a fondue jacuzzi or whatever he's into.

Sorry I can't, like, open the main gate for you or anything. Maliwan's still chomping at the bit to get in here, and they'd be all over that like a perfectly seared medium-rare steak. Man, I am hungry. Siege rations are... not great.
Superfan! Ooh, hope ya don't mind me listening in.
But your ECHO encryption is broke as hell!
I had a chat with Katagawa. He thought he could win a war from an anti-grav swimming pool. So I gave him a little push.
No, no, no, no, no—good doggie! AGHHHH!
We need those turrets online! Hurry, Vault Hunter!
We're getting creamed out here!
Can't hold out much longer!
They're swarming all over the place!
There's the command ship! Get those turrets firing!
Figure it out, Rhys!
Any time, Rhys!
Time is of the essence, Rhys!
Hurry it up, brother!
“Zingberry Crunch”. No. “Athenean Vanilla”. No! Dammit! “Chocolate Dill Pickle”? Yes! Woohoohoo! I'm in!
Okay. Okay! Uh, this might actually work. Uh, uh, uh, uh, laser control! Got it!
Oh! You're here! Awesome. Zer0, let them in.
Spinning up the asteroid's reactors... we're only gonna get one shot!
Hohhh, they're on to me! Deploying countermeasures... I can't get a target lock!
Just fire!
Fire the damn thing!
Take your shot!
Shoot the bloody thing!
I got it... I got it... Target locked! FIRING!
Oh no, oh no! Waghgh! Oh no!||Vault Hunter. Zer0's trying to kill me. He's the traitor! I know, I can hardly believe it myself!
Well done, Vault Hunter. / Thank you for saving my bro. / That creep is finished.
It's the best thing anyone has done to their face, ever. It deserves a medal.
It's a triumph for facial hair everywhere, never again to be surpassed.
Its glory is unrivaled, its shining countenance sublime. The stars in the sky have gone dim, for all their brilliance is here, on your face. It's... pretty sweet.
It's perfection itself. I am happy, nay, proud to call you my mustachioed brother.
I hate it. I want to carve it off your lip with a chisel.||—Just my opinion.
It's the worst thing that's ever happened to me, and anyone else who has to look at you.
It fills me with a revulsion I normally hold for plague vermin, or a beached whale, stuffed with expired mayonnaise, left to rot in the scorching sun of a dying planet. Merely my own opinion.
Brother, I'm gonna be honest. If my mustache looked like yours, I'd have airlock'd myself into space by now.
Oh, come on!
Let's check in with Rhys. He said he's got intel on the final Key fragment.
Zer0? They're here, buddy. Open up the door!
Easy, Liam—the Vault Hunter's with me. VIP, all access.
Oh—sorry, sir! Wow, a real Vault Hunter. Right away, sir!
What? What's that supposed to mean?!
Gah! Vault Hunter—get to the secondary defense control and get our turrets back online!
Oh, damn it—nullhounds! We can't reboot the turrets while their fields are active. Take them out!
Whoa-whoa, VIP only!
I am VIP, you human paperweight.
Oh, I'm VIP. Don't you know who I am?
I am very important. Stand aside.
I am a VIP! Do you need a bribe or somethin'?
Ooh, VIP, look at you! Movin' up in the world. Don't forget about us boots on the ground when you've got a corner office above cloud level.
Great, now Zer0's missing?! I guess I'll buzz you in myself because the CEO has to do ALL THE WORK around here!
Come up to my office/museum-grade aquarium and I'll get you that tasty Key fragment. Now I just have to find where Zer0 disappeared to.
Welcome to Atlas! Rebuilt this place from the foundations. The old Atlas was just a pile of glassed sand and bankruptcy filings when I got here.
What the hell? That was the defense command center! Oh no...
Wow. Okay. That's, uh... a lot to take in.||Thank you, Vault Hunter. I will remember that. Here you go, one Vault Key fragment, as promised.
Dialing in Rhys Strongfork! Man, what a cool name! I bet his ancestors didn't get bullied at all!
